This paper deals with the problem of online matroid intersection, which is a fundamental problem in the area of algorithms and combinatorial optimization. The paper presents a randomized online algorithm that beats the previously known half competitiveness bound. This result is of interest to several subfields of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), game theory (cs.GT), information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
